body:
  My testcase
```verilog
// t_blknblk.v
module t (
    clk
);
    input     clk;

    reg       i_pre;
    reg       i_post;
    reg       o_pre;
    reg       o_post /*verilator public_flat_rw*/;
    reg [1:0] ff;

    always @ (posedge clk) begin
        i_post  <= i_pre;
    end
    always @ (*) begin
        ff[0]   =  i_post;
    end
    always @ (posedge clk) begin
        ff[1]   <= ff[0];
        o_pre   <= ff[1];
        o_post  <= o_pre;
    end
endmodule
```
  Verilator reports BLKANDNBLK warning as compiling the above rtl code. but I insist the rlt code is pretty normal, so I turn it off.
  The following cpp code is generated by verilator-4.040 with `--cc --Wno-BLKANDNBLK`
```cpp
// obj_dir/Vt_blknblk.cpp
// ...
VL_INLINE_OPT void Vt_blknblk::_sequent__TOP__1(Vt_blknblk__Syms* __restrict vlSymsp) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vt_blknblk::_sequent__TOP__1\n"); );
    Vt_blknblk* const __restrict vlTOPp VL_ATTR_UNUSED = vlSymsp->TOPp;
    // Variables
    CData/*1:0*/ __Vdly__t__DOT__ff;
    // Body
    __Vdly__t__DOT__ff = vlTOPp->t__DOT__ff;
    vlTOPp->t__DOT__i_post = vlTOPp->t__DOT__i_pre;
    vlTOPp->t__DOT__o_post = vlTOPp->t__DOT__o_pre;
    __Vdly__t__DOT__ff = ((1U & (IData)(__Vdly__t__DOT__ff))
                          | (2U & ((IData)(vlTOPp->t__DOT__ff)
                                   << 1U)));
    vlTOPp->t__DOT__o_pre = (1U & ((IData)(vlTOPp->t__DOT__ff)
                                   >> 1U));
    vlTOPp->t__DOT__ff = ((2U & (IData)(vlTOPp->t__DOT__ff))
                          | (IData)(vlTOPp->t__DOT__i_post)); // <1>
    vlTOPp->t__DOT__ff = __Vdly__t__DOT__ff;                  // <2>
}
// ...
```
  As you can see above, the order of codes noted by  `<1>` and `<2>` are incorrect.  
  The previous assignment`<1>` is overwritten by the following assignment`<2>`.  

---

  In my opinion, `V3Order` leads to this problem when 2 conditions are met.
  1. `<1>` has smaller ranking result than `<2>`
  2. LogicVertex of `<1>` is moved to a sequential domain.

  In `V3Order`, it seems that you didn't consider the dependency between `COMBO LogicVertex` and `SEQUENT LogicVertex` when they drive the same `VarLogic`, while building the graph.

  I think this is definitely a issue. Can you fix this in a later version？Or give me some advices?

  Thanks a lot.
